RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 4F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 24500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JERSEY JET was hustled clear and to the inside approaching the bend then steadily opened up in the lane while kept to urging until the final seventy yards. TIGGER ATTACK reluctant to load, progressed two wide on the turn, fanned out to path five for the stretch run, altered outside WILDISH inside the final eighth, closed well and caught the latter for second at the wire. WILDISH broke alertly but soon retreated from inside, angled out through the bend, took over second inside the last eighth, drifted out some approaching the final sixteenth, kept a straight path in the waning yards but was outfinished for the place. JILL ATTACK also reluctant to load into the gate, pressed JERSEY JET from just outside, was no match for that one when set down for the drive and flattened out the final eighth. BEST MAN SPEECH was reluctant to load as well, chased from outside, was steadied and altered out when TIGGER ATTACK came into his path nearing the sixteenth marker and had no late bid. COOGAN chased from between horses and was never a factor. MOCOWBELL saved ground and had little to offer for the stretch run. IT'S ON hesitated then broke inward, was three wide taking the bend and empty for the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: It's On
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated, broke inward, 3 wide turn, empty stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Coogan
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased between, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Wildish
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-4 path turn, had 2nd inside 1/8, drifted out some nearing 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Best Man Speech
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-6 path turn, steadied, altered out inside 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Jersey Jet
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: much the best, driving

ENTRY.NAME: Jill Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 2 wide, flattened out late

ENTRY.NAME: Mocowbell
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled in turn, no late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Tigger Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5 wide into stretch, altered out inside 1/8, closed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 56. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIMA ZULU bumped from the rear at the break, moved clear of the rest after the first sixteenth, showed the way in hand just off the inside, was put to a drive midstretch, lugged in some with a sixteenth to go and kept WINDIGO SPIRIT at bay. WINDIGO SPIRIT gradually angled to the inside on the backstretch, moved clear for second on the bend, still loomed a threat with a furlong left, did not have enough late but was clearly second best. MARY'S BOY was hustled along between rivals in the early going, came four wide into the lane, gained third deep stretch then could only hold his position late. BRASKA was soon well back and well off the inside, lost ground widest through the turn but showed a willingness to run the final furlong. HE'S A FINE MAN broke inward, bumping LIMA ZULU then failed to menace in a ground-saving trip. LORD SHAFTESBURY pressed from outside on the backstretch, began to retreat three wide on the bend, swung out to path five for the drive, lugged in upper stretch and continued to fade.

ENTRY.NAME: Lima Zulu
ENTRY.COMMENT: quickly clear, 2-path, steady urging last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: He's a Fine Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Windigo Spirit
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, angled out 1/16, best of rest

ENTRY.NAME: Braska
ENTRY.COMMENT: passed outside tired ones

ENTRY.NAME: Mary's Boy
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-4 path turn, got 3rd 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Lord Shaftesbury
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed outside, 3-5 wide turn, gave way stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 58. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OKLAHOMA HEAT settled just off the inside, commenced his bid after a half mile, came into contention two wide on the second turn, lugged in some as he took a slight advantage inside the furlong marker and gradually edged ahead as he drifted out in the waning yards. SAFE shared the early lead just off the rail while in hand, moved ahead on the second bend, floated out some for the stretch run, began to gradually drift out inside the last eighth, lost the lead, held a straight path the final sixteenth but had to settle for second best. THACKER FROMM rated from inside, went for the lead along the rail after four furlongs, took over third on the second turn, threatened midstretch. angled out for a clear path inside the final eighth then continued to drift as he flattened out late. BLEEDING BLUE displayed early speed outside SAFE but flattened out for the drive. WAVE THE GOLD was a brief contender but gradually yielded from just off the inside before finishing a half mile. AWINBENEATHMYWINGS did not settle into a racing stride into the first bend, showed no speed once he regained a better stride leaving the first turn, was urged along but never really responded.

ENTRY.NAME: Safe
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path speed, drifted out inside 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Wave the Gold
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path, thru early

ENTRY.NAME: Thacker Fromm
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle move inside, flattened out last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Oklahoma Heat
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, 2-path bid after /2, edged ahead inside 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Bleeding Blue
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 3-4 path 2nd turn, flattened out stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Awinbeneathmywings
ENTRY.COMMENT: rank early, urged throughout, no response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 16000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. No n-winners Of A Race Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).

CLAIM.OWNER: Martinez Ralph and Martin Paul E

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRIPLE SCOUT shared the early lead inside rivals but off the rail, moved clear when allowed on the bend and maintained full control while kept to task to the wire. I LUV THIS BAR was caught in tight quarters as she vied for the early lead, shuffled back midway on the backstretch, altered out, was four wide through the turn, took over second inside the last eighth then could only hold her position late. THINK BLUE forwardly placed from outside, lost ground widest through the bend, lacked a significant stretch bid but gained third in the waning yards. BETHY in contention from inside, rallied to threaten along the rail midstretch but leveled off the final eighth. MY MORNING GAL displayed early speed from outside but began to yield three wide before finishing a half mile.

ENTRY.NAME: Triple Scout
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-path speed, kept to task late

ENTRY.NAME: Bethy
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, stretch bid, hung

ENTRY.NAME: I Luv This Bar
ENTRY.COMMENT: shuffled back early, 4 wide turn, got 2nd inside 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Think Blue
ENTRY.OWNER: Cappel Sue Hille Don Rosendohl Robert and Mullins Charles
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost ground, mild bid

ENTRY.NAME: My Morning Gal
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 3 wide turn, flattened out stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 85. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COMFORT ME NOW rated off the early speed, found himself boxed in on the second bend, moved to the rail entering the stretch, rallied inside the last furlong, floated out some in the waning yards but gained the advantage nearing the wire. IRISH DECLARATION boxed in early, gained a clear path three wide midway on the backstretch, closed the gap two wide on the second turn, fanned outside TROY OUNCE entering the lane, also rallied deep stretch and edged ahead for second in the final strides. TROY OUNCE vied for the lead from inside, moved clear on the backstretch, floated out some leaving the second bend, drifted out under right-handed pressure after entering the last eighth, was corrected, gradually wore down between rivals in the late going but was easily best of the rest in a game effort. IMPERIAL MOMENT raced in contention from outside for more than five furlongs then began to yield from path three. FLASHY RICHIE failed to menace in a ground-saving trip. ORBITAL STARR showed little running widest of all most his trip.

ENTRY.NAME: Flashy Richie
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Troy Ounce
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, 2-path into stretch,drifted out inside 1/8,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Imperial Moment
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4 path, gave way last 1/4

ENTRY.NAME: Comfort Me Now
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated 2-path, boxed in 2nd turn, rail bid stretch, got up in time

ENTRY.NAME: Irish Declaration
ENTRY.COMMENT: advanced between, 2-3 wide 2nd turn, got 2nd late

ENTRY.NAME: Orbital Starr
ENTRY.COMMENT: wide trip, showed little

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 96. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 18000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF THREE RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FIVE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $15,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs. ; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Claiming Races For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COMISKEY PARK was encouraged to share the early lead from inside then allowed to relax, let out leaving the bend and steadily drew off under urging in the lane. W W CRAZY hesitated at the break, was hustled up while toward the outside, five wide into the turn, moved to the rail approaching the end of a half mile, moved clear for second upper stretch, still had an easy striking position with a furlong to go but could only hold his position late. ONE PUTT RICHIE prominent not far off the inside on the backstretch, lost ground four to six wide through the bend, gained third inside the last eighth, was all out but could only close the gap on W W CRAZY in the waning yards. DIAMOND MAXIMUS chased running widest, was six wide into the turn, moved in some midway on the bend, lodged a mild bid from path three in the lane and was getting to ONE PUTT RICHIE nearing the wire. BASEBALL POLITICS shared the lead from outside on the backstretch, did not keep up three wide on the turn and gave way the last two furlongs. UPBEAT MELODY displayed early speed between horses, floated out to path four entering the lane and also gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Comiskey Park
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, drew off stretch

ENTRY.NAME: One Putt Richie
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost ground, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: W W Crazy
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated start,hustled, angled in turn,rail bid, not enough left

ENTRY.NAME: Upbeat Melody
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, 2-4 path turn, gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Diamond Maximus
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased outside, angled in turn, 3-path into stretch, mild bid

ENTRY.NAME: Baseball Politics
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 3-5 wide turn, gave way last 1/4

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 57. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WARM BEAUTY rated running widest on the backstretch, was roused five wide on the bend, lost further ground fanning to path seven entering the stretch, rallied under steady urging and got up in time under a well-judged ride. TEMPLUNA was hustled to stay close just off the inside, moved to the rail on the turn, drew clear upper stretch, began to gradually drift out after entering the last furlong and was outfinished. LOUIE P without early speed, though urged along leaving the gate, came into contention four wide on the bend, fanned out further for the drive, threatened with a furlong to go but leveled off in the waning yards. SWEET JUSTICE fractious in the gate before the break, was prominent between rivals from the start, took the turn three wide, floated out some into the lane and gradually yielded deep stretch. BAILESTON LASSIE shared the early lead from outside, moved ahead and stayed just off the inside on the bend but flattened out for the stretch run. TWO MORE TIMES broke alertly but was soon outrun, moved to the inside into the turn, came off the rail some nearing the end of a half mile, swung five wide into the stretch and made up minor ground the final furlong. SUPERTRIX void of speed, though urged along from the early going, was just off the inside on the bend, lost considerable ground fanning to the middle of the track entering the lane and showed belated interest the last eighth. DEAUVILLE MIST disputed the pace from inside on the backstretch but began to fade before finishing three furlongs.

ENTRY.NAME: Deauville Mist
ENTRY.COMMENT: faded inside turn

ENTRY.NAME: Templuna
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled in turn, drew clear stretch, gradual drift last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Louie P
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-5 wide turn, loomed, hung

ENTRY.NAME: Supertrix
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost ground, mild bid

ENTRY.NAME: Two More Times
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide 1/4, 5-path into stretch, mild gain

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Justice
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious gate, 3-4 path turn, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Warm Beauty
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated outside, 5-7 path turn, up in time

ENTRY.NAME: Baileston Lassie
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside speed, 2 wide turn, flattened out stretch
